Rich, is there any timing issues?

it happens intermitently. I have never been able to reproduce it. It is a
possible race condition in DebugPlugin's LaunchManager. It only ever occurs once
in a session. If you then go try to do it again everything is fine (except if
the error occurred while launching a BeanInfo project remote vm, then you would
need to close/reopen the project).

There is a table which initializes the source container types
(initalizeSourceContainerTypes). If two threads at once get in there and one
gets far enough to create the map but has not yet started to fill it in and the
other comes there, it will get an empty map. The
JavaSourceDirector.sourceContainersChanged() method never expects to have
containers, but the containers type hasn't been initialized yet. I'm thinking
that may be what happened here. That is the only way I can think that we could
get an NPE at this point.
